## Important Constraints

### Code Style

- Follow the existing code style and patterns
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Ensure proper type annotations (avoid `any` when possible)
- Write meaningful variable and function names
- Add JSDoc comments for public APIs

### Testing Requirements

- Write tests for all new features and bug fixes
- Maintain or improve code coverage
- Tests should be deterministic and not rely on external state

### Dependencies

- Minimize adding new dependencies
- Prefer well-maintained packages with good security records
- Document why new dependencies are needed in PR descriptions

### Performance Considerations

- Be mindful of bundle size impact
- Avoid synchronous operations that could block
- Consider memory usage for large data processing

### Security Guidelines

- Never commit secrets, API keys, or credentials
- Use environment variables for sensitive configuration
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs
- Keep dependencies updated for security patches

